      "amount": "2 tbsp",
      "notes": "gluten‑free tamari"
    },
    {
      "name": "sesame seeds",
      "amount": "10 g",
      "notes": "lightly toasted"
    },
    {
      "name": "brown sugar",
      "amount": "1 tsp",
      "notes": "optional for balance"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 200°C.",
    "Pat fish fillets dry and season lightly with salt and pepper.",
    "Combine minced lemongrass, garlic, chili, lime juice, cilantro, tamari, sesame seeds, and brown sugar in a bowl to make a paste.",
    "Melt goose fat in a skillet and spread it evenly over a baking sheet.",
    "Place the fish fillets on the sheet and spread the aromatic paste on top of each fillet.",
    "Roast for 20 minutes until the fish flakes easily and the exterior is crisp.",
    "Let the fish rest for 3 minutes before serving.",
    "Serve with extra lime wedges and a sprinkle of fresh cilantro."
  ],
